name: Bushwick Bill
bio__summary: Richard Stephen Shaw (December 8, 1966 – June 9, 2019) was a Jamaican-American rapper and record producer better known by his stage name Bushwick Bill. He was best known as a member of the pioneering Texas hip hop group Geto Boys, a group he originally joined as a dancer in 1986 as Little Billy.

name: Seagram
bio__summary: Seagram Miller (April 13, 1970 – July 31, 1996) was an American rapper from Oakland, California. Miller was shot to death in a drive-by shooting on July 31, 1996.

name: Big Hawk
bio__summary: John Edward Hawkins (November 15, 1969 – May 1, 2006), better known as H.A.W.K. or Big Hawk was an American rapper from Houston, Texas and a founding member of the late DJ Screw's rap group the Screwed Up Click.

name: Fat Pat
bio__summary: Patrick Lamark Hawkins (December 4, 1970 – February 3, 1998), better known by his stage name Fat Pat was an American rapper from Houston, Texas.

name: Big Moe
bio__summary: Kenneth Doniell Moore (August 20, 1974 – October 14, 2007), better known by his stage name Big Moe, was an American rapper from Houston, Texas.

name: Nipsey Hussle
bio__summary: Ermias Asghedom (August 15, 1985 – March 31, 2019), better known by his stage name Nipsey Hussle (often stylized as Nipsey Hu$$le), is an American rapper from Crenshaw, Los Angeles, California. Hussle was murdered outside his store, Marathon Clothing, in South Los Angeles on March 31, 2019.

name: Lord Infamous
bio__summary: Ricky T Dunigan (November 17, 1973 – December 20, 2013), better known by his stage name Lord Infamous, was an American rapper from Memphis, Tennessee. He was best known as co-founder of the Memphis rap group Three 6 Mafia.

name: The Jacka
bio__summary: Dominick Newton (August 12, 1977 – February 2, 2015), better known by his stage name The Jacka, was an American rapper from Pittsburg, California. The Jacka got his start with his group, Mob Figaz.

name: Proof
bio__summary: eShaun Dupree Holton (October 2, 1973 – April 11, 2006), better known by his stage name Proof, was an American rapper and actor from Detroit, Michigan. He was a member of the groups D12. He was a close childhood friend of rapper Eminem. In 2006, Proof was shot and killed during an altercation at the CCC nightclub in Detroit.

name: Big Pun
bio__summary: Christopher Lee Rios[1] (November 10, 1971 – February 7, 2000), known has Big Pun (short for Big Punisher), was an American rapper from The Bronx, New York City, he was the first Latino rapper to have an album certified platinum as a solo act.

name: Big L
bio__summary: Lamont Coleman (May 30, 1974 – February 15, 1999), best known by his stage name Big L, was an American hip hop recording artist from Harlem New York.

name: Guru
bio__summary: Keith Edward Elam (July 17, 1961 – April 19, 2010), better known by his stage name Guru, was an American rapper best known as a member of the hip-hop duo Gang Starr, along with DJ Premier.

name: DJ Screw
bio__summary: Robert Earl Davis, Jr. (July 20, 1971 – November 16, 2000), better known by his stage name DJ Screw, was an American hip hop DJ based in Houston, Texas. He was known has the creator of the now-famous chopped and screwed DJ technique.

name: Soulja Slim
bio__summary: James Adarryl Tapp, Jr. (September 9, 1977 – November 26, 2003), better known by his stage name Soulja Slim (previously Magnolia Slim), was an American rapper and songwriter from New Orleans. He  was shot by an unknow gunman on Thanksgiving Eve in the front row of his mother home.

name: Aaliyah
bio__summary: Aaliyah Dana Haughton (January 16, 1979 – August 25, 2001) was an American singer, dancer, actress, and model from Detroit, Michigan. On August 25, 2001, Aaliyah and eight others were killed in a plane crash in the Bahamas.

name: Mac Miller
bio__summary: Malcolm James McCormick (January 19, 1992 - September 7, 2018), best known by his stage name Mac Miller, is an American rapper.

name: Nate Dogg
bio__summary: Nathaniel Dwayne Hale (August 19, 1969 – March 15, 2011), better known by his stage name Nate Dogg, was an American rapper, singer. He was known as one of the pioneers of West Coast hip hop.

name: Koopsta Knicca
bio__summary: Robert Cooper Phillips (April 27, 1975 – October 9, 2015), better known by his stage name Koopsta Knicca, was an American rapper. He was best known as one of the members of the Memphis rap group Three 6 Mafia.

name: J Dilla
bio__summary: James Dewitt Yancey, better known by the stage names J Dilla and Jay Dee, was an American record producer and rapper who emerged from the mid-1990s underground hip hop scene in Detroit.

name: Ol' Dirty Bastard
bio__summary: Russell Tyrone Jones better known under his stage name Ol' Dirty Bastard (or ODB), was an American rapper and producer. He was one of the founding members of the Wu-Tang Clan.

name: Pimp C
bio__summary: Chad Lamont Butler, better known by his stage name Pimp C, was an American hip hop recording artist and producer. He was best known for his work with Bun B as a founding member of the Underground Kingz (UGK).

name: Mac Dre
bio__summary: Andre Louis Hicks (July 5, 1970 – November 1, 2004), better known by his stage name Mac Dre, was an American rapper and record producer. On November 1, 2004, Mac Dre was fatally shot and killed by an unknown assailant after a performance in Kansas City, Missouri.

name: Eazy-E
bio__summary: Eric Lynn Wright (September 7, 1964 – March 26, 1995), better known by his stage name Eazy-E, was an American rapper who performed solo and in the hip hop group N.W.A. Wright is affectionately called "The Godfather of Gangsta Rap". He was born to Richard and Kathie Wright in Compton, California.

name: The Notorious B.I.G.
bio__summary: Christopher George Latore Wallace (May 21, 1972 – March 9, 1997), better known by his stage names The Notorious B.I.G., Biggie, or Biggie Smalls, was an American rapper.

name: 2Pac
bio__summary: Tupac Amaru Shakur born Lesane Parish Crooks; June 16, 1971 – September 13, 1996), also known by his stage names 2Pac and Makaveli, was an African-American rapper,.

name: Fredo Santana
bio__summary: Derrick Coleman (July 4, 1990 – January 19, 2018), better known by his stage name Fredo Santana, was an American rapper from Chicago, Illinois.

name: Bankroll Fresh
bio__summary: Trentavious Zamon White Sr. (August 2, 1987 – March 4, 2016), better known by his stage name Bankroll Fresh or Yung Fresh, was an American rapper from Atlanta, Georgia.
